#Core Features of Machine Learning:

Supervised Learning — Learning from labeled data (input-output pairs). Your project uses this: predicting pass/fail from student attributes.

Unsupervised Learning — Finding patterns in unlabeled data (e.g., clustering, dimensionality reduction).

Feature Extraction — Selecting and transforming relevant input variables. Your project extracts 19 features like G1, G2, study time, absences.

Model Training — Fitting a model to data by optimizing parameters (e.g., weights in logistic regression or neural networks).

Evaluation Metrics — Measuring model quality: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, Confusion Matrix. All implemented in your project.

Classification vs Regression — Classification predicts categories (pass/fail), regression predicts continuous values (exact grade). Your project does binary classification.

Feature Importance — Understanding which variables most influence predictions. Your project shows G2, G1, and failures as top predictors.

Backpropagation — The algorithm ANNs use to learn by propagating errors backward through layers to update weights.

Overfitting/Underfitting — Balancing model complexity: too complex = memorizes noise, too simple = misses patterns.

Generalization — The ability of a trained model to perform well on unseen data.
